# Single source of truth

- **Do not duplicate any default or config value.** Every constant, default, or config (URLs, feature flags, limits, etc.) must live in exactly one place in the codebase.
- Prefer **code** as that place (e.g. a named constant). Env or config files should only override, not re-state the same default.
- If adding a new default: define it once (typically in the app that uses it), and have docs/env reference it (e.g. "leave unset for default" or "see DEFAULT_X in src/...").
- When you find the same value in two places, remove the duplicate and keep the single canonical definition.

# Follow user instructions

- **Do not remove, delete, or strip out** code, config, comments, or env vars that the user did not ask to remove. Make only the change the user asked for.
- **Do not disobey the user.** When they specify how something should work or what to document, do it that way. Do not introduce optional flows or extra options they did not ask for.
- When in doubt, ask or make the minimal change.
